<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-12T09:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-12T09:29:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2138</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-12T18:00:00+03:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 13, 6
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>471. To President <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>:</p>
                            <p>Sir: We hope you include Russia, while replying to Germany’s request
                                for armistice, among Powers whose territories [are] to be cleared of
                                invaders, since we have repudiated treaty of Brest Litovsk and
                                continued at war with Central Powers. We consider ourselves allies
                                of you and other Allied Powers. Signed, President Government
                                Northern Russia, member Ufa Directory of Five, <persName corresp="#p_CN1">Nicholas</persName> Tchaikowski.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>